{
  "stem": "22944.4",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "A pregnant woman was put on the transport, and he gave her a seat.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And, of course, he was travelling for days, now standing.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "He found a little corner to sit on a train, but a woman came in with a-- pregnant woman, and he stood up and gave her the place to sit down.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "So the whole journey, he was standing.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "That kind of man, he was.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] When he got into [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Auschwitz-- I think it was Auschwitz-- he met my brother, I was told.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "My brother was taken by the-- a prisoner of war by the Russians.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "Uh-- by the German, but that Russian soldier.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "Sorry.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "He was in a-- in a group of Russian prisoners.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And, of course, they also survived.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "I'm very envious of this lot, because they had to treat the Russian prisoners slightly better, because they may need an exchange, or they didn't know that the war is going to develop.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "Apparently, he met my father.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And, on one or two occasion, marching around, and threw him some bread over the fence, the electric fence.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "This is what we were told.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Some people who-- there was an organization that-- people coming back.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Some people survived, and some people met them on their journey.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We don't know-- I don't know the person itself, but they told our family.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And my father then was moved to the Austrian-Hungarian [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] border, to a concentration camp called Ebensee.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There he worked in a cement factory.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And, uh-- tortured, and died.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 7 SECONDS] And that's what we got.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I went back to Ebensee to-- to put a stone up for him, years later, strange enough.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Do you know what happened to your brother?",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
